      "writtenOn": "2021-02-05T18:08:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "in the uniform handler determineIfUsePushContants it says we \"may\" not know if we need the RTHeight Uniform or not. Is there still a decision done in SKSL whether it is needed or is it passed on this fFlipY setting here? If it is this setting it seems like we do know since we\u0027re telling it what to do. If the SkSL compiler still gets to pick how does it notify us at this level so that we have the right size of the pushContants in the layoutCreateInfo?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 218,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 218,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "4d2f0cf524dcaaafe8a7af7469ca765e38d3c227",
